    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Definition uniformly_continuous {X Y : Type}\n  {usX : UStructure X} {usY : UStructure Y} (p : X -> Y)\n  := forall (m : nat),\n      {n : nat & forall u v : X, u =[n] v -> p u =[m] p v}.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n(** In the case that the target has the trivial uniform structure, it is useful to state uniform continuity by providing the specific modulus, which now only depends on the function. *)\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Definition is_modulus_of_uniform_continuity {X Y : Type} {usX : UStructure X}\n  (n : nat) (p : X -> Y)\n  := forall u v : X, u =[n] v -> p u = p v.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
